==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Connective
<hw>Con*nect"ive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Connecting, or
adapted to connect; involving connection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Connection tissue</b></col> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <cd>See
<cref>Conjunctive tissue</cref>, under
<er>Conjunctive</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Connective</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Connective
<hw>Con*nect"ive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which connects</def>.
Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Gram.)</fld> <def>A word that connect
words or sentences; a conjunction or preposition.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>That part of an anther which connects its
thec⟦ae⟧, lobes, or cells.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Connectively</ent>⟦br⟧
